---
description: Universal Finch rules. Loaded on every prompt.
alwaysApply: true
---

Finch is a Tauri v2 + React 19 desktop AI chat app.

- Remote: `origin` → private `Finch_full`. Branches: `main` (Windows), `linux` (Linux laptop).
- Read `.planning/STATE.md` at session start (protocol in `02-session-startup.mdc`).
- Stores: `useChatStore`, `useProfileStore`, `useModelParams`, `useStudioStore`. Never add a 5th. No React Context for global state (`ModalProvider` is the sole exception).
- Alias `@/` resolves to project root, NOT `src/`. Primitives: `@/components/ui/`. App: `@/src/components/`.
- Surgical edits only. Never output full file contents unless asked. Never rewrite a file outside scope.
- Every `#[command]` requires `allow-{kebab-case-name}` in `src-tauri/capabilities/default.json` or it fails silently at runtime.
